  body
    h1
      | GMaps.js add and remove layers - Layers
    .row
      .span11
        #map
      .span6
        p
          | You can easily add or remove a layer using GMaps.js:
        pre
          | var map = new GMaps({ el: '#map', lat: -12.043333, lng: -77.028333 }); map.addLayer('weather', { clickable: false }); map.addLayer('clouds'); 
        p
          span.label.notice
            | Note: 
          |  You can choose 
          strong
            | different layers
          | . Possible values are 
          strong
            | weather
          | , 
          strong
            | clouds
          | , 
          strong
            | traffic
          | , 
          strong
            | transit
          |  and/or 
          strong
            | bicycling
        p
          span.label.notice
            | Note: 
          |  Be aware that you have to add the library 'weather' in the url for the weather/clouds layer: 
        pre
          | http://maps.google.com/maps/api/js?sensor=true&libraries=weather
        p
          span.label.notice
            | Note: 
          |  In the second param you can add your options for the layer as object.
        p
          span.label.notice
            | Note: 
          |  To remove a layer you can use 
        pre
          | map.removeLayer('clouds');
